quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,25,"“What is the matter with you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>that you do not help one another?”"
  37,26,"Rather, on this day, they are submissive."
  37,27,"And they came<a class=""sup""><sup>g </sup></a>to one another, asking one another."
  37,28,"They{1}said, “Indeed, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>used to come at us from the right{2}”",footnotes:1:The misled.|2:This may mean that they used to force them or convince them of the rightness of their deeds.
  37,29,"They{1}said, “Rather, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>yourselves were not believers,",footnotes:1:Those who misled.
  37,30,"and we had no authority over you; rather, you yourselves were a people who exceeded all limits."
  37,31,"And therefore we deserved our Lord’s decree on us. Most surely we will all get a taste,"
  37,32,"for we deluded you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>; indeed, we were deluded.”"
  37,33,"So on that day, they are indeed partners in the punishment."
  37,34,"This is what We do with the criminals."
  37,35,"Indeed, when it was said to them, “There is no god except Allah,” they would act arrogantly"
  37,36,"and say, “Are we really to abandon our gods for a mad poet?”"
  37,37,"In fact, he came with the truth, and he confirmed the emissaries."
  37,38,"Most surely, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>will taste the painful punishment,"
  37,39,"and in no way will you be repaid except for what you used to do,"
  37,40,"except for Allah’s <span class=""h"">sincere chosen<sup foot_note=""80972"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>servants."
  37,41,"For those, there is a known provision:"
  37,42,"fruits, and they are honored"
  37,43,"in the Gardens of Bliss,"
  37,44,"on couches facing one another."
  37,45,"A drink is passed round among them from a flowing spring:"
  37,46,"white, a delight to those who drink,"
  37,47,"no headiness in it, nor <span class=""h"">by it are they<sup foot_note=""80973"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>drained{2}.",footnotes:2:A metaphor for being drunk.
  37,48,"And with them are bashful maidens with lovely eyes,"
  37,49,"as if they were closely guarded eggs."
  37,50,"So they came{1}to one another, asking one another.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered upon by the reader.
  37,51,"One of them said, “Indeed, I did have a comrade"
